NAME
       pacgem - Install Ruby Gems using the Arch Linux Package Manager (pacman)

SYNOPSIS
       pacgem [options] gems...

DESCRIPTION
       Pacgem  allows  direct  installation  of  ruby gems under Arch Linux.  It generates a temporary PKGBUILD which is converted to a
       package file.  The package file is installed using `sudo pacman`.

       -d, --destdir DIR
              Destination directory for package files

       -n, --noinstall
              Do not install package files

       --trace
              Show a full traceback on error

       -h, --help
              Show help message

EXAMPLES
       pacgem --noinstall rack    Create ruby-rack package in the directory ./ruby-rack

       pacgem rack-1.0            Create temporary ruby-rack package and install it

       pacgem 'rack>1.0'          Different version specification

       pacgem thin 'rack~>1.0'    Different version specification

AUTHOR
       Daniel Mendler (mail at daniel-mendler.de)

Based on gem2arch by crabtw (https://github.com/crabtw/abs-tree/tree/master/gem2arch-ruby)
